back into foster care.

11:51.570 --> 11:52.748
I know it's not ideal,
but this isn't just about you.

11:52.772 --> 11:56.440
Your baby's gonna need food
and a roof over its head.

11:56.509 --> 11:57.308
Unless they keep 'em
out in the yard,

11:57.376 --> 11:59.743
Feed 'em whatever
the dogs don't want.

11:59.812 --> 12:00.511
I'll talk to the social worker,

12:00.579 --> 12:03.280
Make sure you find a good home.

12:03.349 --> 12:04.359
No one wants to adopt
a 16yearold.

12:04.383 --> 12:07.952
Even if you do get
a good home in foster care,

12:08.020 --> 12:08.786
Everyone keeps getting
passed along,

12:08.855 --> 12:09.787
Until you finally
end up some place.

12:09.856 --> 12:12.723
Where they'd rather cash
a check from the state.

12:12.792 --> 12:13.691
Than feed you.

12:13.759 --> 12:17.194
Yeah, they're the ones
who keep you forever.

12:20.633 --> 12:21.643
Nat, we really need
those antibiotics.

12:21.667 --> 12:25.069
Okay, I'll be back
as soon as I can.

12:25.138 --> 12:26.003
Yeah.

12:26.072 --> 12:29.240
Okay, keep breathing,
keep breathing.

12:29.309 --> 12:30.041
Okay? Keep breathing.

12:30.109 --> 12:32.577
Just try to relax. It's okay.

12:32.645 --> 12:33.645
Dr. Rhodes?

12:42.689 --> 12:45.056
What's wrong?

12:45.125 --> 12:47.992
Luke's lfts are rising.

12:48.061 --> 12:49.227
What... what does that mean?

12:49.295 --> 12:53.231
